        <div id="comment_body_43320753" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>You appear to have missed "hydrates" - minerals with chemically bound water.  See table 5 (p44) at <a href="http://www.higp.hawaii.edu/~escott/Scott%20Krot%20TOG2007.pdf" title="hawaii.edu">http://www.higp.hawaii.edu/~escott/Scott%20Krot%20TOG2007.pdf</a> <span class="domain-text"> [hawaii.edu]</span>   Many of the minerals listed contain bound water, or OH components which can be driven off by heating.</p></div>
